{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"In 1994, I walked into a prison in Cambodia,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and I met a 12-year-old boy"},{"time":8000,"text":"who had been tortured"},{"time":10000,"text":"and was denied access to counsel."},{"time":12000,"text":"And as I looked into his eyes, I realized"},{"time":14000,"text":"that for the hundreds of letters I had written"},{"time":16000,"text":"for political prisoners, that I would never have"},{"time":19000,"text":"written a letter for him,"},{"time":21000,"text":"because he was not a 12-year-old boy who"},{"time":23000,"text":"had done something important for anybody."},{"time":25000,"text":"He was not a political prisoner."},{"time":27000,"text":"He was a 12-year-old boy who had"},{"time":29000,"text":"stolen a bicycle."},{"time":31000,"text":"What I also realized at that point was that"},{"time":33000,"text":"it was not only Cambodia, but"},{"time":35000,"text":"of the 113"},{"time":37000,"text":"developing countries that torture,"},{"time":39000,"text":"93 of these countries have all passed laws"},{"time":42000,"text":"that say you have a right to a lawyer"},{"time":44000,"text":"and you have a right not to be tortured."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"And what I recognized was that there was an"},{"time":49000,"text":"incredible window of opportunity for us"},{"time":51000,"text":"as a world community to come together"},{"time":54000,"text":"and end torture as an investigative tool."},{"time":57000,"text":"We often think of torture as being"},{"time":59000,"text":"political torture or reserved for"},{"time":61000,"text":"just the worst, but, in fact,"},{"time":64000,"text":"95 percent of torture today"},{"time":66000,"text":"is not for political prisoners."},{"time":68000,"text":"It is for people who are"},{"time":70000,"text":"in broken-down legal systems,"},{"time":72000,"text":"and unfortunately because torture is"},{"time":74000,"text":"the cheapest form of investigation --"},{"time":76000,"text":"it's cheaper than having a legal system,"},{"time":78000,"text":"cheaper than having a lawyer"},{"time":80000,"text":"and early access to counsel --"},{"time":82000,"text":"it is what happens most of the time."},{"time":84000,"text":"I believe today that it is possible for us"},{"time":86000,"text":"as a world community, if we make a decision,"},{"time":89000,"text":"to come together and end torture"},{"time":91000,"text":"as an investigative tool in our lifetime,"},{"time":94000,"text":"but it will require three things."},{"time":96000,"text":"First is the training, empowerment,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and connection of defenders worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"The second is insuring that there is"},{"time":105000,"text":"systematic early access to counsel."},{"time":108000,"text":"And the third is commitment."},{"time":111000,"text":"So in the year 2000,"},{"time":113000,"text":"I began to wonder,"},{"time":116000,"text":"what if we came together?"},{"time":119000,"text":"Could we do something"},{"time":121000,"text":"for these 93 countries?"},{"time":123000,"text":"And I founded International Bridges to Justice"},{"time":125000,"text":"which has a specific mission of"},{"time":127000,"text":"ending torture as an investigative tool"},{"time":130000,"text":"and implementing due process rights"},{"time":132000,"text":"in the 93 countries by placing trained lawyers"},{"time":135000,"text":"at an early stage in police stations"},{"time":137000,"text":"and in courtrooms."},{"time":139000,"text":"My first experiences, though, did come"},{"time":141000,"text":"from Cambodia, and at the time I remember"},{"time":144000,"text":"first coming to Cambodia and there were,"},{"time":146000,"text":"in 1994, still less than"},{"time":148000,"text":"10 attorneys in the country because"},{"time":150000,"text":"the Khmer Rouge had killed them all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"And even 20 years later, there was only"},{"time":154000,"text":"10 lawyers in the country, so consequently"},{"time":156000,"text":"you'd walk into a prison and"},{"time":158000,"text":"not only would you meet 12-year-old boys,"},{"time":160000,"text":"you'd meet women and you'd say,"},{"time":162000,"text":"\"Why are you here?\" Women would say,"},{"time":164000,"text":"\"Well I've been here for 10 years because"},{"time":166000,"text":"my husband committed a crime, but they can't find him.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"So it's just a place where there was no rule of law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"The first group of defenders came together"},{"time":173000,"text":"and I still remember, as I was training, I said,"},{"time":175000,"text":"\"Okay, what do you do for an investigation?\""},{"time":177000,"text":"And there was silence in the class, and finally"},{"time":179000,"text":"one woman stood up, [inaudible name],"},{"time":181000,"text":"and she said \"Khrew,\" which means \"teacher.\""},{"time":184000,"text":"She said, \"I have defended more than"},{"time":187000,"text":"a hundred people, and I've never had to do"},{"time":190000,"text":"any investigation,"},{"time":192000,"text":"because they all come with confessions.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"And we talked about, as a class, the fact that"},{"time":197000,"text":"number one, the confessions"},{"time":199000,"text":"might not be reliable, but number two,"},{"time":201000,"text":"we did not want to encourage the police"},{"time":203000,"text":"to keep doing this, especially"},{"time":205000,"text":"as it was now against the law."},{"time":207000,"text":"And it took a lot of courage for these"},{"time":209000,"text":"defenders to decide that they would"},{"time":211000,"text":"begin to stand up and support each other"},{"time":213000,"text":"in implementing these laws."},{"time":216000,"text":"And I still remember the first cases where"},{"time":218000,"text":"they came, all 25 together, she would"},{"time":220000,"text":"stand up, and they were in the back, and"},{"time":222000,"text":"they would support her, and the judges kept"},{"time":224000,"text":"saying, \"No, no, no, no, we're going to do things"},{"time":226000,"text":"the exact same way we've been doing them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"But one day the perfect case came, and it"},{"time":230000,"text":"was a woman who was a vegetable seller,"},{"time":232000,"text":"she was sitting outside of a house."},{"time":234000,"text":"She said she actually saw the person"},{"time":237000,"text":"run out who she thinks stole"},{"time":239000,"text":"whatever the jewelry was, but the police"},{"time":241000,"text":"came, they got her, there was nothing on her."},{"time":243000,"text":"She was pregnant at the time. She had"},{"time":245000,"text":"cigarette burns on her. She'd miscarried."},{"time":247000,"text":"And when they brought her case"},{"time":249000,"text":"to the judge, for the first time he stood up"},{"time":251000,"text":"and he said, \"Yes, there's no evidence"},{"time":253000,"text":"except for your torture confession"},{"time":255000,"text":"and you will be released.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"And the defenders began to take cases"},{"time":259000,"text":"over and over again and"},{"time":261000,"text":"you will see, they have step by step began"},{"time":264000,"text":"to change the course of history in Cambodia."},{"time":267000,"text":"But Cambodia is not alone."},{"time":269000,"text":"I used to think, well is it Cambodia?"},{"time":271000,"text":"Or is it other countries?"},{"time":273000,"text":"But it is in so many countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"In Burundi I walked into a prison and it wasn't"},{"time":278000,"text":"a 12-year-old boy, it was an 8-year-old boy"},{"time":281000,"text":"for stealing a mobile phone."},{"time":283000,"text":"Or a woman, I picked up her baby,"},{"time":285000,"text":"really cute baby, I said \"Your baby is so cute.\""},{"time":288000,"text":"It wasn't a baby, she was three."},{"time":290000,"text":"And she said \"Yeah, but she's why I'm here,\""},{"time":292000,"text":"because she was accused of stealing"},{"time":294000,"text":"two diapers and an iron for her baby and"},{"time":296000,"text":"still had been in prison."},{"time":298000,"text":"And when I walked up to the prison director,"},{"time":300000,"text":"I said, \"You've got to let her out."},{"time":302000,"text":"A judge would let her out.\""},{"time":304000,"text":"And he said, \"Okay, we can talk about it,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but look at my prison. Eighty percent"},{"time":308000,"text":"of the two thousand people here"},{"time":310000,"text":"are without a lawyer. What can we do?\""},{"time":312000,"text":"So lawyers began to courageously"},{"time":314000,"text":"stand up together to organize a system"},{"time":317000,"text":"where they can take cases."},{"time":319000,"text":"But we realized that it's not only the training"},{"time":321000,"text":"of the lawyers, but the connection"},{"time":323000,"text":"of the lawyers that makes a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"For example, in Cambodia, it was that"},{"time":327000,"text":"[inaudible name] did not go alone"},{"time":329000,"text":"but she had 24 lawyers with her"},{"time":331000,"text":"who stood up together. And in the same way,"},{"time":333000,"text":"in China, they always tell me,"},{"time":335000,"text":"\"It's like a fresh wind in the desert"},{"time":337000,"text":"when we can come together.\""},{"time":339000,"text":"Or in Zimbabwe, where I remember Innocent,"},{"time":341000,"text":"after coming out of a prison where everybody"},{"time":343000,"text":"stood up and said, \"I've been here"},{"time":345000,"text":"for one year, eight years, 12 years"},{"time":347000,"text":"without a lawyer,\""},{"time":349000,"text":"he came and we had a training together"},{"time":351000,"text":"and he said, \"I have heard it said\" --"},{"time":354000,"text":"because he had heard people mumbling"},{"time":356000,"text":"and grumbling -- \"I have heard it said that"},{"time":358000,"text":"we cannot help to create justice"},{"time":361000,"text":"because we do not have the resources.\""},{"time":363000,"text":"And then he said, \"But I want you to know"},{"time":365000,"text":"that the lack of resources"},{"time":368000,"text":"is never an excuse for injustice.\""},{"time":370000,"text":"And with that, he successfully"},{"time":372000,"text":"organized 68 lawyers who have been"},{"time":375000,"text":"systematically taking the cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"The key that we see, though, is training"},{"time":380000,"text":"and then early access."},{"time":382000,"text":"I was recently in Egypt, and was inspired"},{"time":384000,"text":"to meet with another group of lawyers,"},{"time":386000,"text":"and what they told me is that they said,"},{"time":388000,"text":"\"Hey, look, we don't have police"},{"time":390000,"text":"on the streets now. The police are"},{"time":392000,"text":"one of the main reasons why we had"},{"time":394000,"text":"the revolution. They were torturing everybody"},{"time":396000,"text":"all the time.\""},{"time":398000,"text":"And I said, \"But there's been tens of millions"},{"time":400000,"text":"of dollars that have recently gone in"},{"time":402000,"text":"to the development of the legal system here."},{"time":404000,"text":"What's going on?\""},{"time":406000,"text":"I met with one of the development agencies,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and they were training prosecutors"},{"time":411000,"text":"and judges, which is the normal bias,"},{"time":413000,"text":"as opposed to defenders."},{"time":415000,"text":"And they showed me a manual which"},{"time":417000,"text":"actually was an excellent manual."},{"time":419000,"text":"I said, \"I'm gonna copy this.\""},{"time":421000,"text":"It had everything in it. Lawyers can come"},{"time":423000,"text":"at the police station. It was perfect."},{"time":425000,"text":"Prosecutors were perfectly trained."},{"time":427000,"text":"But I said to them, \"I just have one question,"},{"time":429000,"text":"which is, by the time that everybody got to"},{"time":431000,"text":"the prosecutor's office, what had happened to them?\""},{"time":433000,"text":"And after a pause, they said,"},{"time":435000,"text":"\"They had been tortured.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"So the pieces are,"},{"time":439000,"text":"not only the training of the lawyers, but"},{"time":441000,"text":"us finding a way to systematically implement"},{"time":444000,"text":"early access to counsel, because they are"},{"time":447000,"text":"the safeguard in the system"},{"time":449000,"text":"for people who are being tortured."},{"time":452000,"text":"And as I tell you this, I'm also aware of the"},{"time":454000,"text":"fact that it sounds like, \"Oh, okay, it sounds"},{"time":456000,"text":"like we could do it, but can we really do it?\""},{"time":459000,"text":"Because it sounds big."},{"time":461000,"text":"And there are many reasons why I believe it's possible."},{"time":464000,"text":"The first reason is the people on the ground"},{"time":467000,"text":"who find ways of creating miracles"},{"time":470000,"text":"because of their commitment."},{"time":472000,"text":"It's not only Innocent, who I told you about"},{"time":475000,"text":"in Zimbabwe, but defenders all over the world"},{"time":478000,"text":"who are looking for these pieces."},{"time":481000,"text":"We have a program called JusticeMakers,"},{"time":484000,"text":"and we realized there are people that are"},{"time":486000,"text":"courageous and want to do things, but"},{"time":488000,"text":"how can we support them?"},{"time":490000,"text":"So it's an online contest where it's only"},{"time":492000,"text":"five thousand dollars if you come up with"},{"time":494000,"text":"and innovative way of implementing justice."},{"time":496000,"text":"And there are 30 JusticeMakers"},{"time":498000,"text":"throughout the world, from Sri Lanka"},{"time":500000,"text":"to Swaziland to the DRC, who with"},{"time":503000,"text":"five thousand dollars do amazing things,"},{"time":506000,"text":"through SMS programs,"},{"time":508000,"text":"through paralegal programs,"},{"time":510000,"text":"through whatever they can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"And it's not only these JusticeMakers,"},{"time":516000,"text":"but people we courageously see"},{"time":518000,"text":"figure out who their networks are"},{"time":521000,"text":"and how they can move it forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"So in China, for instance, great laws"},{"time":525000,"text":"came out where it says police cannot"},{"time":528000,"text":"torture people or they will be punished."},{"time":531000,"text":"And I was sitting side by side with one of our"},{"time":534000,"text":"very courageous lawyers, and said,"},{"time":537000,"text":"\"How can we get this out? How can we"},{"time":539000,"text":"make sure that this is implemented?"},{"time":541000,"text":"This is fantastic.\" And he said to me,"},{"time":543000,"text":"\"Well, do you have money?\" And I said,"},{"time":545000,"text":"\"No.\" And he said, \"That's okay,"},{"time":547000,"text":"we can still figure it out.\""},{"time":549000,"text":"And on December 4, he organized"},{"time":551000,"text":"three thousand members"},{"time":553000,"text":"of the Youth Communist League,"},{"time":555000,"text":"from 14 of the top law schools,"},{"time":557000,"text":"who organized themselves, developed"},{"time":559000,"text":"posters with the new laws, and went"},{"time":561000,"text":"to the police stations and began what he says"},{"time":563000,"text":"is a non-violent legal revolution"},{"time":566000,"text":"to protect citizen rights."},{"time":569000,"text":"So I talked about the fact that we need"},{"time":571000,"text":"to train and support defenders."},{"time":573000,"text":"We need to systematically implement"},{"time":575000,"text":"early access to counsel."},{"time":577000,"text":"But the third and most important thing is that"},{"time":579000,"text":"we make a commitment to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"And people often say to me, \"You know,"},{"time":583000,"text":"this is great, but it's wildly idealistic."},{"time":585000,"text":"Never going to happen.\""},{"time":587000,"text":"And the reason that I think that"},{"time":589000,"text":"those words are interesting is because"},{"time":591000,"text":"those were the same kinds of words"},{"time":593000,"text":"that were used for people who decided"},{"time":595000,"text":"they would end slavery, or end apartheid."},{"time":597000,"text":"It began with a small group of people"},{"time":599000,"text":"who decided they would commit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Now, there's one of our favorite poems"},{"time":603000,"text":"from the defenders, which they share"},{"time":605000,"text":"from each other, is:"},{"time":607000,"text":"\"Take courage friends, the road is often long,"},{"time":609000,"text":"the path is never clear,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and the stakes are very high,"},{"time":613000,"text":"but deep down, you are not alone.\""},{"time":615000,"text":"And I believe that if we can come together"},{"time":618000,"text":"as a world community to support not only"},{"time":620000,"text":"defenders, but also everyone in the system"},{"time":623000,"text":"who is looking towards it,"},{"time":625000,"text":"we can end torture as an investigative tool."},{"time":628000,"text":"I end always, because I'm sure the questions are --"},{"time":630000,"text":"and I'd be happy to talk to you"},{"time":632000,"text":"at any point -- \"But what can I really do?\""},{"time":634000,"text":"Well, I would say this. First of all,"},{"time":636000,"text":"you know what you can do. But second of all,"},{"time":638000,"text":"I would leave you with the story of Vishna,"},{"time":640000,"text":"who actually was my inspiration"},{"time":643000,"text":"for starting International Bridges to Justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"Vishna was a 4-year-old boy when I met him"},{"time":648000,"text":"who was born in a Cambodian prison"},{"time":650000,"text":"in Kandal Province. But because he was"},{"time":653000,"text":"born in the prison, everybody loved him,"},{"time":655000,"text":"including the guards, so he was the only one"},{"time":657000,"text":"who was allowed to come"},{"time":659000,"text":"in and out of the bars."},{"time":661000,"text":"So, you know, there's bars. And by the time"},{"time":663000,"text":"that Vishna was getting bigger,"},{"time":665000,"text":"which means what gets bigger? Your head gets bigger."},{"time":667000,"text":"So he would come to the first bar,"},{"time":669000,"text":"the second bar and then the third bar,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and then really slowly move his head"},{"time":673000,"text":"so he could fit through, and come back,"},{"time":675000,"text":"third, second, first. And he would"},{"time":677000,"text":"grab my pinkie, because what he wanted"},{"time":679000,"text":"to do every day is he wanted to go visit."},{"time":681000,"text":"You know, he never quite made it to"},{"time":683000,"text":"all of them every day, but he wanted to visit"},{"time":685000,"text":"all 156 prisoners. And I would lift him,"},{"time":687000,"text":"and he would put his fingers through."},{"time":689000,"text":"Or if they were dark cells, it was like iron"},{"time":691000,"text":"corrugated, and he would put his fingers through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"And most of the prisoners said that he was"},{"time":695000,"text":"their greatest joy and their sunshine, and they"},{"time":697000,"text":"looked forward to him. And I was like,"},{"time":699000,"text":"here's Vishna. He's a 4-year-old boy."},{"time":701000,"text":"He was born in a prison with almost nothing,"},{"time":703000,"text":"no material goods, but he had a sense of"},{"time":705000,"text":"his own heroic journey, which I believe"},{"time":707000,"text":"we are all born into. He said,"},{"time":709000,"text":"\"Probably I can't do everything."},{"time":711000,"text":"But I'm one. I can do something."},{"time":713000,"text":"And I will do the one thing that I can do.\""},{"time":715000,"text":"So I thank you for having the prophetic"},{"time":717000,"text":"imagination to imagine the shaping"},{"time":720000,"text":"of a new world with us together,"},{"time":722000,"text":"and invite you into this journey with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}